{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-01",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_01_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Spade and Archer",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 262.5,
  "page_end_sec": 512.72,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.685,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 262.5,
      "end": 262.6,
      "text": "Yes?"
    },
    {
      "start": 264.47,
      "end": 266.0,
      "text": "I don't know where she met him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 266.46,
      "end": 266.74,
      "text": "I mean,"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.78,
      "end": 268.06,
      "text": "I don't know where in New York."
    },
    {
      "start": 268.928,
      "end": 269.24,
      "text": "She's five",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 269.24,
      "end": 270.14,
      "text": "years younger than I,"
    },
    {
      "start": 270.28,
      "end": 271.06,
      "text": "only 17,"
    },
    {
      "start": 271.5,
      "end": 273.52,
      "text": "and we didn't have the same friends."
    },
    {
      "start": 274.44,
      "end": 275.78,
      "text": "I don't suppose we've ever been",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 275.78,
      "end": 277.14,
      "text": "as close as sisters should be."
    },
    {
      "start": 278.016,
      "end": 279.14,
      "text": "Mama and Papa are in Europe.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 280.16,
      "end": 280.86,
      "text": "It would kill them.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 281.62,
      "end": 282.28,
      "text": "I've got to get her",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 282.28,
      "end": 283.4,
      "text": "back before they come home."
    },
    {
      "start": 284.16,
      "end": 284.96,
      "text": "Yes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 285.18,
      "end": 285.78,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 286.88,
      "end": 288.28,
      "text": "They're coming home the first of the month.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 289.504,
      "end": 289.9,
      "text": "Spade's eyes",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 290.28,
      "end": 290.66,
      "text": "brightened."
    },
    {
      "start": 290.7,
      "end": 291.98,
      "text": "Then we've two weeks,"
    },
    {
      "start": 292.2,
      "end": 292.68,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 293.44,
      "end": 296.32,
      "text": "I didn't know what she had done until her letter came.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 297.04,
      "end": 298.12,
      "text": "I was frantic.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 298.32,
      "end": 299.7,
      "text": "Her lips trembled."
    },
    {
      "start": 300.09,
      "end": 303.1,
      "text": "Her hands mashed the dark handbag in her lap."
    },
    {
      "start": 303.57,
      "end": 304.9,
      "text": "I was too afraid she"
    },
    {
      "start": 304.9,
      "end": 306.84,
      "text": "had done something like this to go to the police,"
    },
    {
      "start": 307.54,
      "end": 309.14,
      "text": "and the fear that something had happened to her",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 309.22,
      "end": 310.32,
      "text": "kept urging me to go."
    },
    {
      "start": 310.64,
      "end": 313.26,
      "text": "There wasn't anyone I could go to for advice."
    },
    {
      "start": 313.72,
      "end": 315.28,
      "text": "I didn't know what to do."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.82,
      "end": 316.94,
      "text": "What could I do?"
    },
    {
      "start": 317.88,
      "end": 318.48,
      "text": "Nothing,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 318.64,
      "end": 319.1,
      "text": "of course,"
    },
    {
      "start": 319.26,
      "end": 319.9,
      "text": "Spade said."
    },
    {
      "start": 320.62,
      "end": 321.54,
      "text": "But then her letter came.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 322.45,
      "end": 323.0,
      "text": "Yes,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 323.2,
      "end": 325.86,
      "text": "and I sent her a telegram asking her to come home."
    },
    {
      "start": 326.54,
      "end": 328.18,
      "text": "I sent it to General Delivery here."
    },
    {
      "start": 328.68,
      "end": 330.52,
      "text": "That was the only address she gave me."
    },
    {
      "start": 331.0,
      "end": 332.56,
      "text": "I waited a whole week,"
    },
    {
      "start": 332.94,
      "end": 333.88,
      "text": "but no answer came."
    },
    {
      "start": 334.66,
      "end": 335.82,
      "text": "Not another word from her.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 336.62,
      "end": 339.48,
      "text": "And Mama and Papa's return was drawing nearer and nearer.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 340.3,
      "end": 342.06,
      "text": "So I came to San Francisco to get her.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 342.8,
      "end": 343.72,
      "text": "I wrote her I was coming.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 344.51,
      "end": 345.76,
      "text": "I shouldn't have done that,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 345.8,
      "end": 346.16,
      "text": "should I?"
    },
    {
      "start": 347.552,
      "end": 347.92,
      "text": "Maybe not.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 348.92,
      "end": 350.68,
      "text": "It's not always easy to know what to do.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 351.1,
      "end": 352.36,
      "text": "You haven't found her?"
    },
    {
      "start": 352.7,
      "end": 353.84,
      "text": "No,"
    },
    {
      "start": 353.92,
      "end": 354.84,
      "text": "I haven't."
    },
    {
      "start": 355.14,
      "end": 357.18,
      "text": "I wrote her that I would go to the St."
    },
    {
      "start": 357.26,
      "end": 357.54,
      "text": "Mark,"
    },
    {
      "start": 357.88,
      "end": 360.0,
      "text": "and I begged her to come and let me talk to her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 360.06,
      "end": 362.3,
      "text": "even if she didn't intend to go home with me."
    },
    {
      "start": 363.14,
      "end": 363.86,
      "text": "But she didn't come.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 364.96,
      "end": 365.92,
      "text": "I waited three days,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 366.12,
      "end": 366.96,
      "text": "and she didn't come."
    },
    {
      "start": 367.34,
      "end": 368.96,
      "text": "Didn't even send me a message"
    },
    {
      "start": 369.14,
      "end": 369.72,
      "text": "of any sort."
    },
    {
      "start": 371.072,
      "end": 372.96,
      "text": "Spade nodded his blonde Satan's head,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 373.18,
      "end": 374.64,
      "text": "frowned sympathetically,"
    },
    {
      "start": 374.72,
      "end": 375.68,
      "text": "and tightened his lips"
    },
    {
      "start": 375.8,
      "end": 376.02,
      "text": "together."
    },
    {
      "start": 377.12,
      "end": 377.71,
      "text": "It was horrible,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 378.4,
      "end": 379.14,
      "text": "Miss Wonderly said,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 379.2,
      "end": 379.98,
      "text": "trying to smile."
    },
    {
      "start": 380.78,
      "end": 381.9,
      "text": "I couldn't sit there like that,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 382.3,
      "end": 382.72,
      "text": "waiting,"
    },
    {
      "start": 383.84,
      "end": 385.28,
      "text": "not knowing what had happened to her,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 386.02,
      "end": 387.48,
      "text": "what might be happening to her.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 388.38,
      "end": 389.02,
      "text": "She stopped trying",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 389.16,
      "end": 389.52,
      "text": "to smile."
    },
    {
      "start": 390.2,
      "end": 390.9,
      "text": "She shuddered."
    },
    {
      "start": 391.16,
      "end": 393.6,
      "text": "The only address I had was General Delivery."
    },
    {
      "start": 394.24,
      "end": 395.34,
      "text": "I wrote her another letter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 395.46,
      "end": 397.64,
      "text": "and yesterday afternoon I went to the post office."
    },
    {
      "start": 397.9,
      "end": 399.94,
      "text": "I stayed there until after dark,"
    },
    {
      "start": 400.26,
      "end": 400.92,
      "text": "but I didn't see"
    },
    {
      "start": 401.0,
      "end": 401.12,
      "text": "her."
    },
    {
      "start": 401.74,
      "end": 405.3,
      "text": "I went there again this morning and still didn't see Corinne,"
    },
    {
      "start": 405.82,
      "end": 407.04,
      "text": "but I saw Floyd Thursby."
    },
    {
      "start": 408.352,
      "end": 409.16,
      "text": "Spade nodded again.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 410.52,
      "end": 411.54,
      "text": "His frown went away.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 412.28,
      "end": 414.49,
      "text": "In its place came a look of sharp attentiveness.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 415.44,
      "end": 417.12,
      "text": "He wouldn't tell me where Corinne was,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 417.34,
      "end": 418.66,
      "text": "she went on hopelessly."
    },
    {
      "start": 418.74,
      "end": 420.14,
      "text": "He wouldn't tell me anything,"
    },
    {
      "start": 420.62,
      "end": 422.28,
      "text": "except that she was well and happy."
    },
    {
      "start": 423.1,
      "end": 424.22,
      "text": "But how can I believe that?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 424.75,
      "end": 425.94,
      "text": "That is what he would tell me"
    },
    {
      "start": 426.02,
      "end": 426.28,
      "text": "anyhow,"
    },
    {
      "start": 426.46,
      "end": 426.94,
      "text": "isn't it?"
    },
    {
      "start": 427.52,
      "end": 428.12,
      "text": "Sure,"
    },
    {
      "start": 428.38,
      "end": 429.32,
      "text": "Spade agreed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 429.56,
      "end": 430.6,
      "text": "but it might be true."
    },
    {
      "start": 431.94,
      "end": 432.78,
      "text": "I hope it is.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 432.88,
      "end": 434.22,
      "text": "I do hope it is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 434.34,
      "end": 435.14,
      "text": "she exclaimed."
    },
    {
      "start": 436.06,
      "end": 439.06,
      "text": "But I can't go back home like this without having seen her,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 439.22,
      "end": 440.52,
      "text": "without even having"
    },
    {
      "start": 440.76,
      "end": 442.0,
      "text": "talked to her on the phone."
    },
    {
      "start": 442.52,
      "end": 443.9,
      "text": "He wouldn't take me to her."
    },
    {
      "start": 444.04,
      "end": 445.6,
      "text": "He said she didn't want to see me."
    },
    {
      "start": 446.06,
      "end": 447.36,
      "text": "I can't believe that."
    },
    {
      "start": 448.09,
      "end": 449.98,
      "text": "He promised to tell her he had seen",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 449.98,
      "end": 452.08,
      "text": "me and to bring her to see me if she"
    },
    {
      "start": 452.08,
      "end": 454.24,
      "text": "would come this evening at the hotel."
    },
    {
      "start": 455.0,
      "end": 456.74,
      "text": "He said he knew she wouldn't.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 457.03,
      "end": 458.52,
      "text": "He promised to come himself"
    },
    {
      "start": 458.58,
      "end": 459.44,
      "text": "if she wouldn't."
    },
    {
      "start": 459.56,
      "end": 460.2,
      "text": "He,"
    },
    {
      "start": 461.02,
      "end": 464.04,
      "text": "she broke off with a startled hand to her mouth as the door opened.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 465.08,
      "end": 465.8,
      "text": "The man who",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 465.8,
      "end": 467.38,
      "text": "had opened the door came in a step,"
    },
    {
      "start": 467.56,
      "end": 467.9,
      "text": "said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 468.2,
      "end": 468.32,
      "text": "oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 468.78,
      "end": 469.64,
      "text": "excuse me."
    },
    {
      "start": 470.56,
      "end": 472.02,
      "text": "Hastily took his brown hat from his",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 472.16,
      "end": 472.9,
      "text": "head and backed out."
    },
    {
      "start": 474.112,
      "end": 474.6,
      "text": "It's all right,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 474.64,
      "end": 474.82,
      "text": "Miles,"
    },
    {
      "start": 475.14,
      "end": 476.02,
      "text": "Spade told him."
    },
    {
      "start": 476.46,
      "end": 476.76,
      "text": "Come in."
    },
    {
      "start": 477.54,
      "end": 478.16,
      "text": "Miss Wonderly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 478.24,
      "end": 479.08,
      "text": "this is Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 479.26,
      "end": 479.54,
      "text": "Archer,"
    },
    {
      "start": 479.6,
      "end": 480.06,
      "text": "my partner."
    },
    {
      "start": 481.472,
      "end": 483.34,
      "text": "Miles Archer came into the office again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 483.5,
      "end": 484.72,
      "text": "shutting the door behind him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 485.344,
      "end": 487.3,
      "text": "ducking his head and smiling at Miss Wonderly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 488.4,
      "end": 490.98,
      "text": "making a vaguely polite gesture with the hat in",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 490.98,
      "end": 491.52,
      "text": "his hand."
    },
    {
      "start": 492.01,
      "end": 493.68,
      "text": "He was of medium height,"
    },
    {
      "start": 494.336,
      "end": 495.08,
      "text": "solidly built,"
    },
    {
      "start": 495.68,
      "end": 496.48,
      "text": "wide in the shoulders,"
    },
    {
      "start": 496.76,
      "end": 497.64,
      "text": "thick in the neck,"
    },
    {
      "start": 498.14,
      "end": 498.32,
      "text": "with a"
    },
    {
      "start": 498.5,
      "end": 498.88,
      "text": "jovial,"
    },
    {
      "start": 498.92,
      "end": 502.22,
      "text": "heavy-jawed red face and some gray in his close-trimmed hair."
    },
    {
      "start": 502.58,
      "end": 504.38,
      "text": "He was apparently as many"
    },
    {
      "start": 504.38,
      "end": 507.08,
      "text": "years past 40 as Spade was past 30."
    },
    {
      "start": 507.26,
      "end": 508.28,
      "text": "Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 509.04,
      "end": 511.18,
      "text": "Miss Wonderly's sister ran away from New York",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 511.18,
      "end": 512.72,
      "text": "with a fellow named Floyd Thursby."
    }
  ]
}